    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "TO : Director, FBI - Attention: Assistant DATE: July 28, 1947",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "Director D. M. LADD",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, San Francisco",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "There is transmitted herewith for the information of the Bureau b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "a report received from Lieutenant [REDACTED], A-2, Hamilton Field,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "California, containing the results of an investigation by his office concerning",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "the reported sighting of flying discs.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "In addition to containing the detailed descriptions of what was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "allegedly seen by several persons, the Bureau's attention is particularly called",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "to the first memorandum setting forth the notes of Agent [REDACTED] CIC,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Fourth Air Force, concerning an interview he had with Mr. [REDACTED] Box b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "387, Boise, Idaho, who reported that on July 12, 1947 he had seen nine strange",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "objects flying over the Cascade Mountain Range of Washington State. It will be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "noted that CIC Agent [REDACTED] reports that \"Mr. [REDACTED] is very outspoken and somewhat",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "bitter in his opinions of the leaders of the United States Army Air Forces and the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "FBI for not having made an investigation of this matter sooner.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "The thought has occurred to me that the Bureau might desire to have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "an agent of the Butte Office contact Mr. [REDACTED] and explain to him our lack of b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
